-- Powerful earthquake rattles Mexico, shakes buildings
-- By Dave Graham
-- Fri Apr 18, 2014 10:44AM EDT
-- None



MEXICO CITY, April 18 (Reuters) - A powerful earthquake struck Mexico on Friday, shaking buildings  in the capital and sending people running out into the street.

The magnitude 7.5 quake was centered in the western state of Guerrero, north of the beach resort of Acapulco, the U.S. Geological Survey said.